## Feature Breakdown

### Feature 0: Vue.js Migration
**Tier:** Feature (Tier 1)  
**Duration:** Ongoing (foundational migration)  
**Status:** 🚧 In Progress - Phases 0.0-0.2 in progress

**Description:**  
Migrate the application from React to Vue.js, establishing the foundation for all other features. This migration includes project setup, data layer, state management, and component conversions.

**Dependencies:** None (foundational migration)

**Reference:** See `.cursor/project-manager/features/vue-migration/VUE_MIGRATION_USER_STORY.md` for complete migration status and detailed phase information. See `.cursor/project-manager/features/vue-migration/feature-vue-migration-guide.md` for feature-level planning and `.cursor/project-manager/features/vue-migration/phases/phase-[N]-guide.md` for detailed phase guides.

**Migration Status:**
- Phase 0.0: Project Setup - ✅ Complete
- Phase 0.1: Data Layer Foundation - 🚧 In Progress
- Phase 0.2: State Management - 🚧 Phase 2.1 Complete
- Phase 0.3: Property System Refactor - ⏳ Not Started
- Phase 0.4: Admin Wizard - ⏳ Not Started (converts Feature 3 - **recommended before Phase 0.5**)
- Phase 0.5: Scheduler Wizard - ⏳ Not Started (converts Feature 2.0 - recommended after Phase 0.4)
- Phase 0.6: React Cleanup and Removal - ⏳ Not Started (final cleanup after all phases complete)

**Impact on Other Features:**
- **Feature 1:** Requires Feature 0 Phases 0.0-0.2 (Vuexy setup, Pinia stores)
- **Feature 2.0:** Requires Feature 0 Phases 0.0-0.2 (Vue foundation)
- **Feature 2:** Will be built entirely in Vue.js (depends on Feature 0 Phase 0.5)
- **Feature 3:** Being converted from React to Vue (Feature 0 Phase 0.4)
- **Feature 4:** Minimal impact - API layer is framework-agnostic

**Success Criteria:**
- Vue 3 + Vite + TypeScript project scaffolded
- Vuexy components integrated
- Pinia and Vue Query configured
- All type definitions ported
- State management stores created
- Component conversions complete

**Note:** This migration is foundational and affects multiple features. Phases 0.0-0.2 must complete before other features can proceed.

