### Feature 1: Core Infrastructure & Layout
**Tier:** Feature (Tier 1)  
**Duration:** 2-3 weeks  
**Status:** 🚧 In Progress - Utilities exist, layout/navigation to be built

**Description:**  
Build the foundational layout, navigation, state management, and core utilities that all other features depend on.

**Dependencies:** None (foundational)

**Migration Impact:**
- **Decision:** Build layout/navigation in Vue.js as part of Feature 0
- **Dependencies:** Feature 0 Phases 0.0-0.2 (Vuexy setup, Pinia stores)
- **Existing React Code:** None - will be built fresh in Vue
- **Note:** Core utilities (`ProfileToFinalTimeUtils`) are framework-agnostic and can be used in Vue

**Current State:**
- ✅ `ProfileToFinalTimeUtils` - Complete time calculation utilities
- ✅ Time calculation types (`timeTypes.ts`, `timeDataUtil.tsx`) - Complete
- 📝 `appointmentTransformer.ts` - Fee calculation logic exists but commented out, needs refactoring
- ⏳ Layout components - Not started (will be built in Vue)
- ⏳ Navigation system - Not started (will be built in Vue)
- ⏳ State management - Architecture planned, implementation needed (will use Pinia stores)

**Success Criteria:**
- Layout components (header, nav, footer, content section) functional
- Navigation system with step tracking
- Core state management structure (Pinia stores)
- Fee calculation engine integrated
- Mobile-first responsive design

**Risk Assessment:**
- **Technical Risks:**
  - Vuexy component library learning curve
  - Pinia store architecture design decisions
  - Fee calculation integration complexity
- **Timeline Risks:**
  - Dependency on Vue migration foundation
  - Refactoring commented-out appointment transformer code
- **Mitigation:**
  - Reference Vuexy documentation and examples
  - Design Pinia store structure before implementation
  - Extract and test fee calculation logic independently

**Testing Strategy:**
- **Unit Tests:** 
  - Fee calculation logic (90%+ coverage)
  - Time calculation utilities
  - State management functions
- **Integration Tests:**
  - Layout component rendering
  - Navigation state transitions
  - State persistence (if implemented)
- **E2E Tests:**
  - Basic navigation flow
  - Mobile responsiveness

**Success Metrics:**
- All utilities functional and tested
- Layout renders correctly on all screen sizes
- Navigation works smoothly
- State management handles all appointment data
- Performance: Layout loads in <1s

**Fallback Plans:**
- If Vuexy components unavailable: Use base Vuetify components
- If Pinia setup delayed: Use Vue 3 Composition API with provide/inject
- If fee calculation integration fails: Use simplified calculation temporarily

