### Feature 2: Customer Booking Wizard
**Tier:** Feature (Tier 1)  
**Duration:** 6-8 weeks  
**Status:** 🚧 In Progress - Architecture complete, waiting on Feature 2.0 UI port

**Description:**  
Integrate business logic and real data into Jose's ported wizard UI (Feature 2.0). We are NOT building our own wizard - we are adapting Jose's complete wizard model. Multi-step wizard allowing customers to select services, provide property details, choose appointment times, enter contact information, and confirm booking.

**Dependencies:** 
- Feature 1 (Core Infrastructure)
- Feature 2.0 (Jose's Wizard UI Port) - Must complete UI port first
- Feature 3 (API Integration Layer) - For Google Calendar, Maps, MLS APIs

**Migration Impact:**
- **Decision:** Will be built entirely in Vue.js (Feature 0 Phase 0.5)
- **Strategy:** Integrate business logic into ported UI from Feature 2.0
- **Dependencies:** Feature 0 Phases 0.0-0.2, Feature 2.0 completion
- **Note:** UI structure comes from Feature 2.0, this feature adds real data and calculations

**Current State:**
- ✅ Architecture decisions documented (`SCHEDULER_ARCHITECTURE_DECISIONS.md`)
- ✅ Component specifications created (`SCHEDULER_COMPONENT_SPECS.md`)
- ✅ Phase 1 implementation guide (`SCHEDULER_PHASE_1_IMPLEMENTATION.md`)
- ✅ ListMaker component exists (`client/src/scheduler/components/listMaker.tsx`) - contains critical filtering logic that should be extracted to composable
- ⏳ Waiting on Feature 2.0 (UI port) to begin business logic integration
- ⏳ Need to integrate real service data from API
- ⏳ Need to integrate availability calculation engine
- ⏳ Need to integrate fee calculation engine

**Success Criteria:**
- All 5 wizard steps functional with real data
- Differential scheduling logic working correctly
- Availability calculations accurate and integrated
- Form validation complete
- API integrations working (Google Calendar, Maps)
- Mobile-responsive design
- End-to-end booking flow functional

**Risk Assessment:**
- **Technical Risks:**
  - Complex availability calculation engine integration
  - Differential scheduling logic complexity
  - API integration failures
  - Real-time availability updates
- **Timeline Risks:**
  - Dependency on Feature 2.0 completion
  - Dependency on API integration (Feature 3)
  - Complex business logic implementation
- **Mitigation:**
  - Build availability engine incrementally
  - Use mock data initially, integrate APIs gradually
  - Test each step independently before integration
  - Implement fallback mechanisms for API failures

**Testing Strategy:**
- **Unit Tests:**
  - Availability calculation logic
  - Fee calculation integration
  - Form validation functions
  - State management updates
- **Integration Tests:**
  - Complete wizard flow
  - API integration (with mocks)
  - State transitions between steps
  - Differential scheduling toggle
- **E2E Tests:**
  - Happy path booking flow
  - Error scenarios (API failures, validation errors)
  - Mobile device testing
  - Differential vs standard scheduling

**Success Metrics:**
- All 5 steps functional with real data
- Availability calculations accurate (within 15-minute tolerance)
- Form validation prevents invalid submissions
- API response times <2s
- Mobile experience smooth (no horizontal scrolling)
- Booking completion rate >80% in testing

**Fallback Plans:**
- Google Calendar API fails → Manual availability entry mode
- Google Maps API fails → Manual address entry (no autocomplete)
- MLS API fails → Manual property details entry
- Availability calculation fails → Show all time slots, let user select
- Fee calculation fails → Show "Contact for pricing" message

---

