## Post-MVP Priority Features

Features from the catalog that are recommended for early post-MVP implementation:

### High Priority (Post-MVP Phase 1)

**Email Notifications** - ✅ Moved to Feature 2 Phase 2.5
- Booking confirmations
- Appointment reminders
- Cancellation notifications
- **Business Value:** High - Reduces no-shows, improves communication
- **Complexity:** Medium - Requires email service integration
- **Dependencies:** Feature 2 completion

**Appointment History (Admin View)** - ✅ Moved to Feature 3
- View past appointments
- Appointment notes
- **Business Value:** High - Essential for business operations
- **Complexity:** Low - Database queries and display
- **Dependencies:** Feature 3 completion

### Medium Priority (Post-MVP Phase 2)

**Rescheduling** - Allow clients/admins to reschedule
- **Business Value:** High - Reduces cancellations
- **Complexity:** Medium - Requires availability recalculation
- **Dependencies:** Feature 2 completion

**Appointment Reminders** - Automated SMS/email reminders
- **Business Value:** High - Reduces no-shows
- **Complexity:** Medium - Requires notification service
- **Dependencies:** Email notifications (Phase 1)

**Client Portal** - Clients view/manage appointments
- **Business Value:** Medium - Self-service convenience
- **Complexity:** High - Requires authentication, portal UI
- **Dependencies:** Feature 2 completion

### Lower Priority (Post-MVP Phase 3+)

- Multiday inspections
- Report Review Second Calendar Date
- Time-first scheduling
- Advanced analytics and reporting
- Payment processing
- Other features from catalog (evaluate as needed)

**Note:** See `.cursor/project-manager/future-features-catalog.md` for complete prioritized list and evaluation framework.

---

