### Important Implementation Notes

1. **Vue Migration Impact (Feature 0):**
   - Active Vue.js migration is in progress (Feature 0 Phases 0.0-0.2)
   - Some features may be implemented in Vue.js rather than React
   - Check Feature 0 status before starting new work
   - See: `.cursor/project-manager/features/vue-migration/` for detailed migration status

2. **Existing Code to Leverage:**
   - `ProfileToFinalTimeUtils` - Time calculation utilities (✅ Complete)
   - `appointmentTransformer.ts` - Fee calculation logic (commented out, needs refactoring)
   - `ListMaker` component - Contains critical filtering logic that should be extracted to a composable
     - **Recommendation:** Extract filtering/selection logic → `useSchedulerFilter` composable
     - **UI:** Use Jose's wizard UI patterns instead of ListMaker's Ant Design UI
     - **Status:** Needs refactoring - filtering logic is business-critical and should be reusable
   - API infrastructure exists in `externalAPI/` and `internalAPI/` directories
   - SchemaProp management system exists (temporary, will be stripped)

3. **SchemaProp Management Feature:**
   - Temporary admin interface for managing schema props (SchemaProp management UI)
   - This is a temporary feature supporting the coding process
   - Will be stripped when converting properties back to straight (non-config-driven)
   - NOT the same as Service/Additional Service/Availability Options configuration

4. **Jose's Wizard Model (Source of Truth - ALWAYS Adapt This):**
   - **Location:** `/Users/districthomepro/Bonsai/Jose-Scheduler-Reference/src/views/pages/wizard-examples/scheduler/`
   - **Status:** ✅ Complete UI implementation with all 5 steps
   - **What's Ready to Port:**
     - ✅ Complete wizard shell with vertical stepper navigation (`index.js`)
     - ✅ Step 1: Service Selection (`StepServiceSelection.js`) - User type, service type, additional services
     - ✅ Step 2: Property Details (`StepPropertyDetails.js`) - Property type, address, details
     - ✅ Step 3: Appointment Availability (`StepAppointmentAvailability.js`) - Calendar, time slots, differential UI
     - ✅ Step 4: Personal Information (`StepPersonalInformation.js`) - Contact forms
     - ✅ Step 5: Price Details (`StepPriceDetails.js`) - Confirmation/summary
     - ✅ State management hook (`useAppointment.js`) - Complete appointment state management
     - ✅ Constants (`Appointment.js`) - Service types, requester types, part types
   - **What Needs Conversion:**
     - ⚠️ Material-UI (MUI) → Vuetify components (when Vuexy support ready)
     - ⚠️ React → Vue.js (Composition API)
     - ⚠️ React hooks → Pinia stores/composables
     - ⚠️ Hardcoded data → Real API integration
     - ⚠️ Simplified logic → Full business logic (availability calculations, fee calculations)
     - ⚠️ react-datepicker → Vue date picker component
   - **Porting Strategy (CRITICAL - We Adapt, Never Build From Scratch):**
     - ✅ ALWAYS start from Jose's components - they are the source of truth
     - ✅ Port Jose's components to Vue/Vuetify (Feature 2.0)
     - ✅ Replace MUI components with Vuetify equivalents (one-to-one mapping)
     - ✅ Integrate with real data sources and business logic (Feature 2)
     - ✅ Enhance with full differential scheduling calculations
     - ✅ Add API integrations (Google Calendar, Maps, MLS)
     - ❌ NEVER build our own service selection wizard or wizard components
     - ❌ NEVER start from scratch - always adapt Jose's model

