## Feature Handoff Summaries

Quick reference for transitioning between features or handing off to team members.

### Feature 1 Handoff: Core Infrastructure & Layout
**Current Status:** 🚧 In Progress  
**Next Phase to Start:** Phase 1.1 (Layout & Navigation Structure)  
**Key Decisions Made:**
- Build layout/navigation in Vue.js as part of migration
- Use Pinia stores for state management
- Core utilities (`ProfileToFinalTimeUtils`) are framework-agnostic
**Blockers/Dependencies:**
- Waiting on Feature 0 Phases 0.0-0.2 (Vuexy setup, Pinia stores)
**Ready to Handoff:** ⏳ No - Waiting on Feature 0 foundation

### Feature 2.0 Handoff: Jose's Wizard UI Port
**Current Status:** ⏳ Not Started  
**Next Phase to Start:** Phase 2.0.1 (Wizard Shell & Navigation)  
**Key Decisions Made:**
- Port UI structure first, integrate business logic later (Feature 2)
- Replace MUI with Vuetify equivalents
- Convert React hooks to Pinia stores/composables
**Blockers/Dependencies:**
- Must complete Feature 1 first
- Must complete Feature 0 Phases 0.0-0.2
**Ready to Handoff:** ⏳ No - Waiting on dependencies

### Feature 2 Handoff: Customer Booking Wizard
**Current Status:** 🚧 In Progress (Architecture complete)  
**Next Phase to Start:** Phase 2.1 (Service Selection Step)  
**Key Decisions Made:**
- Integrate business logic into ported UI from Feature 2.0
- Use real API data (not hardcoded)
- Implement full differential scheduling calculations
**Blockers/Dependencies:**
- Must complete Feature 2.0 (UI port) first
- Need Feature 4 (API Integration) for Google Calendar, Maps, MLS
**Ready to Handoff:** ⏳ No - Waiting on Feature 2.0 completion

### Feature 3 Handoff: Admin Configuration Interface
**Current Status:** 🔄 Migrating (React version complete)  
**Next Phase to Start:** Phase 3.1 (Service Settings Management)  
**Key Decisions Made:**
- Convert from React to Vue (Feature 0 Phase 0.4)
- Maintain React version until Vue version complete
- Convert components incrementally
**Blockers/Dependencies:**
- Waiting on Feature 0 Phase 0.4 (Vue conversion)
- Depends on Feature 1 (Core Infrastructure)
**Ready to Handoff:** ⏳ No - Waiting on Feature 0 Phase 0.4

### Feature 4 Handoff: API Integration Layer
**Current Status:** 📝 Partial (Infrastructure exists)  
**Next Phase to Start:** Phase 4.1 (Google Calendar API Integration) or Phase 4.2 (Google Maps API Integration) - can run parallel  
**Key Decisions Made:**
- API layer is framework-agnostic
- Can proceed in parallel with other features
- MVP-critical: Google Calendar and Maps APIs
- Post-MVP: MLS API (can defer with manual entry fallback)
**Blockers/Dependencies:**
- Depends on Feature 1 (Core Infrastructure)
- Phase 4.3 (MLS API) depends on Phase 4.2 (Maps API)
**Ready to Handoff:** ✅ Yes - Can start Phase 4.1 or 4.2 once Feature 1 complete

